Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Public Service/Program Assistant ( Permanent Part-Time) Alliston , ON Description Job # 072023-01 Posting Date: July 12, 2023 The New Tecumseth Public Library is now seeking a people-oriented individual to work in all three Branches (Alliston, Tottenham and Beeton) as a Part-Time Public Service/Program Assistant. The successful applicants will be required to work with a very high degree of accuracy, exercise tact and independent judgment in accordance with library policy and must possess demonstrated respect and appreciation for patrons of all ages. It is anticipated that there will be opportunities for additional hours available from time to time, and that the applicant should be available to work at all three branches and have transportation to the same. Requirements: Secondary School Graduation or higher Post-secondary education (e.g. SOLS EXCEL) and/or Library Technician Diploma an asset1 to 2 years clerical/administrative experience; direct experience in public service and/or librariesExcellent communication skills (including reading, writing, listening and speaking skills)Demonstrated excellence in customer service skillsBasic math and computer skills essential Duties: Perform basic Circulation Desk duties.Perform check in/check out of library materials.Respond to basic requests for reference services under supervision. Refer questions to senior staff when necessary.Assist with preparation of received ILLO and SCL materials.Handle money at the circulation desk including fines, photocopying and sale of materials.Refer all user complaints to senior staff or manager as necessary.Process (i.e. apply book jackets, barcodes, spine labels, etc.) and repair library materials.Other duties as may be assigned from time to time. Wage Rate:$25.81 per hour plus 4% vacation pay. Hours of Work: Up to an average of 25 hours per week. Hours and location are subject to change at any time. Base Location: Alliston Memorial Branch (Alliston) Please submit your cover letter and resume in one PDF Document to jmole@ntpl.ca no later than 4:30PM on Friday, July 21, 2023. Please quote Job Posting # CIRC 72023-01 in the subject line of your email. We thank you for your interest, however; only those selected for an interview will be contacted. The New Tecumseth Public Library is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to inclusive, barrier-free recruitment and selection processes. If contacted for an interview, please advise the recruiter if you require accommodation. Compensation $25.81 Closes: 21 July, 2023 New Tecumseth Public Library Alliston , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
