Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager, Regional Programming Halifax , NS Description Halifax Public Libraries invites INTERNAL and EXTERNAL applications for the full-time, permanent position of Manager, Regional Programming.Halifax Public Libraries is an inclusive employer committed to employment equity and building a diverse workforce. We encourage all qualified persons to apply and self-identify. We will accommodate applicants’ needs under the Nova Scotia Human Rights Act throughout all stages of the recruitment and selection process. If you require an accommodation, we will confidentially address your needs. A RESOURCE FOR EVERYONEHalifax Public Libraries engages communities and the people who live in them – encouraging participation, facilitating connections, and providing solutions in an ever-changing world. We provide equal and open access to services to all residents of Halifax Regional Municipality. Under the direction of the Halifax Regional Library Board, the Library provides learning, social, and engagement opportunities through a network of 14 branches, an online presence, community engagement, borrow by mail and home delivery servicesKEY RESPONSIBILITIESThe Manager, Regional Programming is responsible for setting the vision and direction for programming initiatives that span all branches and communities served by Halifax Public Libraries. Under the direction of the Director of the Central District and Regional Programming, they work together with managers across all districts, senior leaders, and the regional and district leads to support the development, implementation and evaluation of region-wide programs.Regional Programming:Responsible for ensuring excellent system-wide programming across all areas including Arts &amp; Culture, Civic Engagement, Children, Teens/Young Adults, Community Learning, and Newcomers Services.Oversees program development, implementation and evaluation while ensuring that programs respond to community needs, address equity &amp; inclusion, and achieve desired outcomes.Upholds principles of intellectual freedom and free expression and ensures a diversity of perspectives and views are reflected and freely expressed in library programs.Undertakes community engagement activities and works closely with Leads and Specialists to support ongoing local engagement.Shares community knowledge with District and branch teams, regional teams, and departments; collaborates to develop responsive services and programs.Develops strategic partnerships to support library programming and participates in the network of service providers.Leads or sponsors teams working on regional initiatives and collaborates with other departments to support regional initiatives.Provides functional support and direction for leads and specialists working in this area.Develops service expertise and serves as a regional resource for service development.Staffing Excellence:Communicates the regional programming vision, strategy, priorities and objectives clearly to all staff.Hires, develops, and coaches direct reports &amp; creates a climate of continuous improvement and innovation to achieve excellent programming outcomesCollaborates with People &amp; Culture team to resolve complex HR issues, develop learning and development plans, paths and initiatives, and support the wellness, health and safety of staff.Fosters a respectful workplace where diversity is valued and where individuals are treated with dignity and respectSupports and shows leadership by working to health and safety standards, following health and safety policies and procedures and encouraging colleagues to work to the same standards by reporting incidents, hazardous conditions and improvement possibilitiesAssessment and Evaluation:Identifies issues, solves problems, designs and implements effective processes.Makes informed decisions and measures achievements by analyzing data and information, taking corrective action when necessary.Works closely with the Manager, Research and Analytics to develop and implement an outcome-based evaluation process to evaluate program effectiveness, equity, and impact, encompassing community, partner and staff perspectives.Resource Allocation and Management:Holds self and teams accountable to achieve results and ensures that regional staffing resources allocated to programming work are used effectively.Seeks opportunities for grants, leads or sponsors applications and monitors grant funds and reportsManages regional programming budgets and monitors expensesEducation and ExperienceGraduate Degree in Library Science or Information plus four (4) years of related experienceSpecific Knowledge &amp; Technical Experience Required:Excellent communication and facilitation skills. Able to read and write in English Demonstrated conflict resolution and customer service skills Strong team and project leadership skillsExperience in program planning and deliveryExperience in community engagement Demonstrated leadership experience and ability to provide instruction, coaching, training and performance managementProficient computer knowledge and skills including Functions of a web browser Microsoft office applications Social media applicationsTRAVEL The job requires travel between our various library branches and community sites within the Halifax Regional Municipality. A driver’s license and/or access to reliable transportation is necessary. CORE COMPETENCIESServing with Care Respect for Diversity, Welcome and Value Inclusion Learning and Growth Mindset Communication Resilience LEADERSHIP COMPETENCIESStrategic thinkingResource ManagementLeading and Developing OthersAccountability**This is a provisional classification, Job Evaluation is pending**Apply Here Compensation $89,222.05 - $104,377.18 Closes: 23 July, 2023 Halifax Public Libraries Halifax , NS Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
