Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Public Services Supervisor - Community Branch Surrey , BC Description Public Services Supervisor – Community Branch Surrey Libraries is an innovative and award-winning library system that provides a wide range of materials, programs, and information services to the community. We are a growing library system, recognized for our ability to respond creatively to our active and diverse community through outreach to community groups and partnerships with agencies. In addition to our collections, progressive use of technology and a wide variety of online resources, we specialize in genealogical materials and multilingual collections in 16 languages. Our 10 branches, together with our website www.surreylibraries.ca serves a population of more than 575,000, offering a wide range of physical and digital items, electronic resources, programs, and services to people of all ages and interests. Overview There is an opening for the position Public Services Supervisor- Community Branch at Port Kells Branch. This is a regular part-time (29.5 hours per week) position. The Public Services Supervisor performs a variety of duties related to providing exceptional customer service and supervision to maintain efficient, welcoming and inclusive library operations of a small branch. This position reports to the Branch Manager and is also accountable to Department Managers.Major Responsibilities and Duties Answers general queries in the branch or community, assisting the public at the point of contact.Schedules and co-ordinates staff to ensure that all programs and services are maintained and that budgeted hours are properly allocated.Answers information services, reader’s advisory and other inquiries.Checks library materials in and out of the system, including using automated tools. Sorts, shelves and cleans library materials.Packs and unpacks materials received from or being shipped to other branches.Completes registrations and resolves issues relating to accounts, programs and events.Prepares and delivers a broad range of programming.Deals with day-to-day facility related issues impacting library operations.Assists and instructs on use of and access to library resources, equipment and technologies. Performs troubleshooting.Collects and records payments of fees and fines.Deals with member queries and complaints concerning their accounts.Explains, interprets and resolves complaints related to Library policies and procedures.Supervises and trains staff reporting to the position; co-ordinates staff meetings, assists in evaluating job performance and in staff selection.Prepares information and answers queries related to staff pay.Participates in various committees and projects. Designs and prepares a variety of visual media e.g., displays, signage, etc. and promotes library services, initiatives and merchandise.Handles and reconciles monies received by the branch, maintains records of receipts and expenditures.Engages and liaises with community organizations in and out of branch to promote library use and increase community engagement.Prepares reports, statistics or other documents.Locates and retrieves materials, such as holds and traces.Participates in collection maintenance duties, e.g. processing, shelf reading and weeding.Assists in materials selection.Keeps library in neat and orderly condition.Performs other related duties.Qualifications, Knowledge, SkillsDiploma in Library Technology from a recognized Library Technician’s program, or an equivalent combination of directly related work experience, training and courses.Successful completion of a course in supervisory practice.Accurate keyboarding speed of 35 words per minute.2 to 3 years work experience in customer service.Knowledge of library resources and collection, as related to the work performed.Knowledge of programming techniques and materials.Knowledge of computer hardware and software applications, and online resources related to the work performed.Knowledge of current trends and best practices in public library services.Excellent customer service skills including strong problem-solving skills required to interpret member needs and offer solutions.Excellent organization and communication skills. Ability to lead, direct, supervise and maintain good working relationships with other staff.Ability to exercise discretion and make decisions under minimal direction. Ability to work with flexibility, creativity, initiative, and accountability.Ability to learn new technologies, applications and software, processes and skills. Ability to complete monetary transactions. Ability to meet physical demands of the work including safe handling of materials.Ability to work positively in a fast paced and challenging environment.Commitment
to continuous development and growth. How to applyA criminal record check, with no conviction of any offence related to the position applied for, is a condition of employment. If you are interested in this opportunity, send your cover letter, resume and unofficial transcript with the subject “Public Services Supervisor – Community Branch” to SPLEmployment@surrey.ca. The deadline is July 20, 2023.We thank in advance all applicants who apply and advise that only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $35.40-$36.26 Closes: 20 July, 2023 Surrey Libraries Surrey , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
