Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Collections and Member Services Manager St. Albert , AB Description Collections and Member Services ManagerJoin us in building community in St. Albert and forging the future of public libraries in Alberta. We are looking for a dynamic leader with a love of stories and reading, a passion for libraries, enthusiasm for community, people smarts and a head full of great ideas.We need a motivated person who wants to do interesting things from a public library platform. Want to build something great? We do too. We are looking for a person who can lead Collections and Member Services, overseeing the functional areas of collection management, membership, material circulation and access services.Key ongoing and upcoming projects include the move from a single to a multiple location system with the Jensen Lakes Library launch, implementation of an operational review’s recommendations on collections and materials management, updating the Library’s barrier-free access plan and putting into action the Library’s new 2023-2028 Strategic Plan: Here for YOU, Here for ALL.Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer,You will be a key member of the Library’s senior Management Team, working with the Community Engagement Manager and Technology and Operations Manager in leading library-wide initiatives.You will contribute to all aspects of service planning and act as CEO when required.You will have ideas on where libraries need to go in the future and the energy, skills and vision to translate ideas into results.You will develop, recommend and implement plans to realize the Library’s goals.You value partnerships and collaboration as you will work with people outside the Library, including vendors, funders, the Board and the community.You are a skilled people manager, able to make the most of your team’s enthusiasm, expertise and abilities. Qualifications:MLS/MLIS or equivalent combination of relevant education and experience.Five years’ experience, including supervisory and management experience, preferably in the areas of collection development and/or circulation.Experience using an ILS system circulation module. Experience with SirsiDynix Horizon is an asset.A commitment to service excellence and community-focussed service delivery.Proficiency with current productivity software (Microsoft Office, Google Workspace).Driver’s license required.Who we are:One of the busiest mid-sized libraries in Canada, St. Albert Public Library is a vital part of the community. It is a place where people learn, meet and share ideas, and enjoy leisure time. St. Albertans are avid readers and learners, and the Library has responded with excellent physical and digital collections, a unique place-based Summer Reading Game, and STARFest, an award-winning literary festival. Library staff love what they do and where they work, some spending their entire careers at SAPL. Where we are:St. Albert, Alberta is a dynamic, beautiful and growing city of over 70,000 people, named the Best Place to Live in Canada. The main library is located in downtown St. Albert on the banks of the Sturgeon River in St. Albert Place, an architectural jewel. One of Alberta’s oldest communities, St. Albert treasures its Francophone, First Nations and Métis heritage. Located on the northwest corner of Edmonton, St. Albert residents have the best of both worlds: a strong small-town sense of community with easy access to big city amenities.Salary band: $97,089 - $119,054 per yearHours of work: Permanent full-time position. 36 hours per week.Closing date: Sunday, July 23, 2023, at 5:00 p.m.Full job description here (click).To apply: Please email cover letter and resume to Rhonda Kozuska, rkozuska@sapl.ca. Compensation $97,089 - $119,054 per year Closes: 23 July, 2023 St. Albert Public Library St. Albert , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V