Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Membership Services Analyst Toronto , ON Description Posting #: 22-479EXTREP2 Posting Date: June 28, 2022 Closing Date: July 06, 2022 Job Title: Membership Services Analyst (Collections &amp; Membership Services) Location: To be determined Status: Permanent Full-Time 35 hours per week. Potential for Hybrid Work Arrangement. Weeks 1 &amp; 2: Mon. to Fri. 9:00 am - 5:00 pm. Membership Services Analyst Are you skilled in data analytics and knowledgeable in public libraries? If so, the Membership Services Analyst role at TPL may be the perfect opportunity for you. As a Membership Services Analyst, you will support and implement membership strategies and conduct research on future membership services and retention strategies. You will analyze data, identify trends, and make recommendations to improve the member experience. With access to member data, you will introduce best practices and make a measurable impact. Our team is dedicated to creating and delivering data-driven member experiences while removing barriers to access to library services. At TPL, you will join a team that values authenticity, welcomes innovative approaches, and works together with both external and internal partners to drive membership strategies. Job Summary: The Analyst is responsible for supporting and implementing membership strategies and conducting research to inform future membership services and retention strategies. The Analyst is also responsible for the day-to-day data &amp; analytics of membership services including regular data reports and working with internal stakeholders to support business needs and strategic goals. Duties: Under the direction of the Manager, Membership and Circulation Services, and working within a team structure, this position is responsible for: Developing and maintaining member data for operational data-informed decision-making and future policy decisions Providing data and reporting of Key Performance Indicators and membership-related trends Supporting evaluation and performance measurement of enterprise membership services and initiatives to ensure a focus on continual improvement and assist the organization in achieving its strategic goals Supporting and implementing membership strategies Conducting research and analysis in deepening the understanding of community and customer needs Supporting cross-divisional initiatives to support the removal of barriers impacting membership Supporting the evaluation and implementation of automated library system applications related to membership services Developing and delivering training on new and existing membership processes and procedures Identifying and assessing needs and recommending solutions to identified needs and problems Writing business cases and briefing memos, and contributing to RFPs, RFQs, RFSs Serving as a resource to project teams, working groups and other departments and committees Maintaining and coordinating contacts with other libraries, service providers, vendors Performing other duties as assigned Qualifications: Graduate degree in Library or Information Science from an accredited institution or equivalent education Minimum of five (5) years’ professional public library experience, including experience in membership and customer services. Strong SQL or Microsoft Excel skills with the ability to learn other analytics tools Proven analytic skills, including evaluation, analysis and visualization Experience with data-management systems working with large data-sets Demonstrated experience with supporting and implementing membership strategies Demonstrated experience and commitment to the removal of barriers impacting membership Knowledge of public library trends and diverse community needs Understanding and appreciation of the philosophy of public service to all, in accordance with human rights legislation and the principles of equity and access in the delivery of library service Ability to perform work requiring independent judgement and initiative Ability to work independently, with a high degree of accuracy and attention to detail Demonstrated sound planning, interpersonal, organizational, analytical, problem-solving, consultative, and training skills Demonstrated ability, skills and experience in working under pressure and developing harmonious relations with staff, customers, and external contacts Proven ability to think conceptually, understand the big picture and convey clearly to others Excellent communication and presentation skills Salary: $73,782.80 per annum (2023 Rate)E-mail your cover letter and resume, quoting the Job Posting #, to recruitment@tpl.ca. We thank all applicants and advise that only those selected for an interview will be contacted. The Toronto Public Library invites applications from all qualified individuals. The Library is committed to employment equity and diversity in the workplace and welcomes applications from racialized people/people of colour, women, Indigenous people, people with disabilities, and 2SLGBTQ+ people. Upon request, accommodation will be provided for persons with disabilities through all stages of the recruitment and selection process. If you require an accommodation to apply to a Toronto Public Library job posting, please send us an email with your accommodation needs at accommodations@tpl.ca quoting the posting number and the title. If you are invited to participate in the assessment process and require accommodations for the assessment, we ask that you provide your accommodation request as soon as reasonably possible. All accommodation requests are confidential. Toronto Public Library does not ask for a credit card, banking information, or social insurance number during the recruitment process. Do not respond to emails or requests for information about jobs at TPL that are not sent from an @tpl.ca address. Compensation $73,782.80 per annum Closes: 26 July, 2023 Toronto Public Library Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
